Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 7;
if (x > 5)
{
    System.out.println("big");
}
System.out.println("done");
```

What is the value of `result` after the following code executes?

```java
int a = 10;
int b = 3;
int result = 0;
if (a % b == 0)
{
    result = 1;
}
else
{
    result = 2;
}
```

What is the output of the following code?

```java
int n = 4;
if (n > 0)
    System.out.println("positive");
    System.out.println("not zero");
```

A programmer wants the output to be `same` when both String variables hold the text `"hello"`. Which of the following correctly identifies why the code below produces `different` instead?

```java
String s1 = new String("hello");
String s2 = new String("hello");
if (s1 == s2)
{
    System.out.println("same");
}
else
{
    System.out.println("different");
}
```

What is the value of `grade` after the following code executes?

```java
int score = 75;
String grade = "";
if (score >= 90)
    grade = "A";
else if (score >= 80)
    grade = "B";
else if (score >= 70)
    grade = "C";
else
    grade = "F";
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 8;
int y = 3;
if (x > 5)
{
    if (y > 5)
    {
        System.out.println("A");
    }
    else
    {
        System.out.println("B");
    }
}
else
{
    System.out.println("C");
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 0;
